definitions.definition: A country in Southern Africa . Official name: Republic of Angola . Capital and largest city: Luanda .

subdefinitions.definition: ( historical ) A former colony of Portugal , Portuguese Angola, also known as Portuguese West Africa and officially the State of West Africa, from 1575 to 1975.
The People's Republic of Angola, from 1975 to 1992

definitions.definition: An unincorporated community in Sussex County , Delaware , United States .
A city , the county seat of Steuben County , Indiana , United States .
An unincorporated community in Labette County , Kansas , United States .
A village in Erie County , New York , United States .
